{"title_page": "Richard Wildash", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}\n'''Richard James Wildash''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|LVO}} (born 24 December 1955) is a British diplomat. Wildash was the British Ambassador to S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe (non-resident) in January 2010 and was also Ambassador to Angola. He has also served as the High Commissioner to Malawi, and as British High Commissioner to Cameroon and non-resident Ambassador to Gabon, Chad, the Central African Republic and Equatorial Guinea. Wildash has a degree in Modern and Mediaeval Languages from Corpus Christi College Cambridge.<ref name=\"govuk\">{{cite web |title=Richard Wildash |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/people/richard-wildash |website=GOV.UL |accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-bef| before = Peter Boon }} \n{{s-ttl| title  = [[List of High Commissioners of the United Kingdom to Cameroon|High Commissioner to Cameroon]]<br />and to other West African countries\n       | years  = 2002\u20132006 }}\n{{s-aft| after  = [[Syd Maddicott]] }}\n{{s-bef| before = [[David Pearey]] }} \n{{s-ttl| title  = [[List of High Commissioners of the United Kingdom to Malawi|High Commissioner to Malawi]]\n       | years  = 2006\u20132009 }}\n{{s-aft| after  = [[Fergus Cochrane-Dyet]] }}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Patricia Phillips (diplomat)|Patricia Phillips]] }} \n{{s-ttl| title  = [[List of Ambassadors of the United Kingdom to Angola|Ambassador to Angola]]<br />and to S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe\n       | years  = 2010\u20132014 }}\n{{s-aft| after  = [[John Dennis (diplomat)|John Dennis]] }}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Roderick Drummond]] }} \n{{s-ttl| title  = Deputy Head of Mission, [[Riyadh]]\n       | years  = 2014\u2013present }}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n==References==\n*{{Who's Who |surname=Wildash |othernames=Richard James |id=U42195 |volume=2016 |edition=Oxford University Press, 2015 online |accessed=16 June 2016